summary_text: 1. I grew up in a neighborhood with Mrs. Baker. 2. Mrs. Baker was the resident cat lady. 3. She had adopted at least twenty cats. 4. Mrs. Baker had a young grandson. 5. I was quite the tomboy back then. 6. Her grandson was trying to befriend me. 7. I didn't take to him much. 8. He had poor manners. 9. He left a note saying he'd run away. 10. Mrs. Baker came to my treehouse. 11. I talked her down from panicking. 12. We decided to search for him. 13. We found his baseball cap near the old mill. 14. We trailed more but found no trace. 15. We returned to the treehouse club. 16. He was sitting on a branch with a comic book. 17. The local sheriff warned me to lay low. 18. I laid low and stayed out of sight.
